article.headline: Detroit 64, Eastern Michigan 60
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Chuck Bailey scored 13 points and Brandon Cotton added 11 Tuesday to lead Detroit Mercy to a 64-60 victory over Eastern Michigan. Torvoris Baker had 10 points for the Titans (3-3). John Bowler and Danny McElhinny scored 19 and 12 points, respectively, for the Eagles (1-2). Trailing 44-37, Eastern went on a 9-2 run to tie the game at 46 with 8:19 left. Detroit immediately responded with a 3-pointer by Jon Goode and a basket by Cotton to go in front for good. The Titans took their largest lead of the game, 55-48, with 4:32 remaining on a basket by Muhammad Abdur-Rahim. The Eagles pulled within 55-54 with 2:36 left following consecutive 3-pointers by Carlos Medlock and McElhinny. But Baker hit a 16-footer and Bailey had a 3-point play to put Detroit ahead 60-54 with 1:29 left. The Titans sealed the win as the Eagles committed back-to-back turnovers in the closing minute. Both teams combined for a poor offensive display in the first half. Detroit and Eastern connected on only 18 of 55 shots from the field and totaled 16 turnovers.
